# [INTROVERT PROJECT PROGRESS REPORT: 01 MAY 2026]

## [EXECUTIVE SUMMARY]
"Introvert" has reached full architectural maturity. As of May 1, 2026, the project has successfully transitioned from a conceptual architectural plan to a fully valid cross-platform ecosystem. The project features a high-performance Rust core bridged via zero-copy FFI to a unified Flutter UI, running a dual-deployed (Devnet & Mainnet) gasless Solana incentive economy. Identity, trust, and asset storage are cryptographically unified.

## [1. MAJOR ACHIEVEMENTS (PRODUCTION LAUNCH)]

### [SOLANA MAINNET ECONOMY (FINALIZED)]
- [PRODUCTION DEPLOYMENT]: Officially deployed the Introvert Token (`INTR`) onto the **Solana Mainnet Beta cluster**.
- [ON-CHAIN MINT]: Initialized Mint Address `EAXT8h2qTtS5RPfAPX3qpbn6b99bqKfNwLKyqZp9ZZPf` with exactly 9 decimals of precision.
- [SUPPLY SEALED]: Minted the fixed initial reward supply of 100,000,000 tokens directly into the Treasury vault and immediately disabled the mint authority.
- [SECURITY ENFORCED]: Removed plain-text JSON keypair files from the active development directory. The master recovery seed phrase was extracted into physical cold storage.

### [DESKTOP ANCHOR DAEMON (INTROVERTD)]
- [HEADLESS CORE]: Successfully extracted the Rust engine from the FFI boundary into a standalone, high-uptime CLI daemon (`introvertd`).
- [BOOTSTRAP CAPABILITY]: Configured the daemon to act as a persistent backbone node, listening on ports 4001 (TCP/QUIC) for incoming peer discovery.
- [INCENTIVE ENGINE]: Developed the `RewardTracker` for autonomous work-proof generation based on relay metrics (bytes relayed, messages forwarded).
- [GASLESS CLAIMS]: Implemented `claim_anchor_reward` logic connecting the Anchor daemon directly to the Solana Mainnet Treasury ATA for automated INTR payouts.
- [STABILITY PROMOTION]: Integrated logic for nodes to self-promote to Anchor status after 30 minutes of stable uptime.

### [P2P NETWORKING & PROTOCOLS]
- [PEER DISCOVERY]: Optimized Kademlia DHT routing for production, enabling zero-knowledge address resolution for ephemeral mobile peers behind NATs.
- [MESSAGE PERSISTENCE]: Implemented SQLCipher-backed `message_queue` for asynchronous store-and-forward delivery.
- [ASYNC ROUTING]: Integrated `direct_messaging` behaviour into the libp2p swarm loop to handle automated message forwarding and caching.
- [P2P AUDIO (VOIP)]: Integrated the Opus audio codec (48kHz, mono) for low-latency, real-time voice communication; implemented bidirectional mic/speaker FFI streaming buffers.

### [UNIFIED FLUTTER CONVERGENCE]
- [DIRECT FFI INTEGRATION]: Realized native-speed communication by pivoting from interpreted wrappers to `dart:ffi` directly mapping Rust heap allocations. Memory leaks resolved via `introvert_free_string`.
- [GLASSMORPHIC VISUAL ENGINE]: Delivered the custom "Blueprint UI" with background grids, message bubbles, and causal branch lines drawn natively over the Canvas using a unified `CustomPainter`.
- [MEDIA CONVERGENCE]: Delivered the real-time **VoIP Calling UI** and **Solana Wallet Dashboard**, fully synchronized with the underlying Opus codec and Solana Mainnet economy.
- [MUTUAL HANDSHAKE UI]: Implemented the 'Mutual Consent Handshake' logic and Contact Discovery UI, enforcing an anti-spam barrier where connections are only established after explicit invitation and acceptance.
- [CHAT UI]: Completed the chronological `ChatScreen` with E2EE message sending and local SQLite history loading.
- [DECENTRALIZED GROUPS]: Implemented the Multi-User Group Chat layer using a custom OR-Set CRDT and Vector Clocks for serverless causal synchronization.

### [SECURITY AUDIT & HARDENING (COMPLETED)]
- [DH RATCHET SECURED]: Removed hardcoded nonces in the Double Ratchet implementation; every message now uses a unique, cryptographically random 12-byte nonce with full forward secrecy.
- [OUT-OF-ORDER DELIVERY]: Implemented skipped message key tracking in the ratchet state, allowing the core to decrypt messages that arrive out of sequence.
- [STORAGE ENCRYPTION]: Verified and enabled SQLCipher PRAGMA keys, ensuring the local database is encrypted on-disk using HKDF-SHA256 derived keys from the user's master Ed25519 identity.
- [FFI RUNTIME STABILITY]: Refactored `EngineState` to persist the Tokio async runtime, preventing background network tasks from being dropped during FFI calls.
- [MESSAGE AUTHENTICITY]: Integrated mandatory cryptographic signing for all `MessageEnvelope` objects, ensuring zero-knowledge relays cannot tamper with metadata or payload.
- [SOLANA ATA PRECISION]: Updated reward logic to derive Associated Token Accounts (ATAs) properly via the `spl-associated-token-account` crate for the production INTR mint.

